Cross Over Color melt. I am loving these colors blended together 😍🤟🏻💞. Its a super fun and customizable technique and placement. For this look I parted the hair in its natural 4 quadrants. Two sections around the face, and in the back sectioned parted down the middle. Then I formulate and keep my color choices diagonal to each other. In this one I went a step further and in between each section I colored a solid gray panel to break it up! Whos ready to try the Cross Over Color melt?!

What I am most grateful for this season is my family. These last 9 years have been absolutely the most rewarding. It matched our struggle like a beautiful dance. Being reminded so often how little we had, and how hard we as a family had to work from the ground up. I remember how hard my husband and I worked to put me through school with no help, I still feel how it felt crying with my husband as he lost his business and I just started an intensive apprenticeship. I remember taking vows that in poverty I would do everything to make our love rich, and in wealth I will do everything not to let our love grow poor. That vow is a line I wrote and although it was always my most felt line I never realized the impact would be a thread of our story and life.
Some how that feels like 3 lives already.In so much time you can forget parts of yourself, and you damn sure loose yourself, parts you will never get back. But I will continue to be thankful for the fight we put in everyday, I will continue to pray for strength and guidance from god, I will continue to be grateful for the shared grace and compassion of those closest to me.And most of all I will continue to stay passionate and motivated to my biggest dreams and goals so that I can continue to leave a positive impact on you all my community, my Riot Squad Pulp Fam, My salon team,my family, my friends, and everyone in between. Excited and thankful to fight another day with all of you. Always remember you have the simplest to be grateful for we have to hold onto that, trust yourself, and search every unlocked door, its supposed to be messy, dont worry about others criticisms because that can cripple you, and most of the time you wont be criticized by someone doing more than you 🤨🧐😉. Live your life, live it well, be good to others. Happy Thanksgiving you guys 🦃♥️🤟🏻🥰.
.

.
.

My page draws a lot of bright creative colors, but natural work has always been a matched passion of mine. 🔥⚗️I am just going to say it.... this industry is an industry where we are given the incredible privilege to serve others. We have direct influences and impacts on trends in our industry and a lot of these trends are really positive. But some are not! ❗️❗️❗️ Some of these amazing tools are causing self serving behaviors, causing and incredible influx of influencers who are over editing photos, especially blondes, leaving extremely unrealistic expectations placed on the backs of stylists, which these stylist’s claim to be experts in. This creates doubts and insecurities in talented every day hair dressers. 💌🌎Were living in a world where modern technology will allow us to talk ourselves into justifying the use of tools to improve hollow areas in or work, placing blurring tools on fades, whitening tools to brighten blondes, all so they can drive business and profit. Look like masters so the industry and others will invest in them, and people are! I have always fought for authenticity and its never kept me from opportunities. The blonde on the right is more beautiful to me because its authentic and untouched, because I continue to grow despite the growing pressure to use tools to make my work look like it jumped off a magazine cover. But I cant stand to see what the trickle down effects are in our industry. I will always support authentic rawness, the real, and a natural beauty approach to how I carry my business and my influence and I hope others will take the stand with me. .
.
.
.

💫 Pro tip about utilizing yellow, and one of my favorite yellow semi Lemon 🍋from #pulpriothair. When lifting the hair before semi’s I always aim for levels 8-9 to utilize the underlying pigment of gold, to support my desired tone, and longevity. 🌊🌬 Confidence without Entitlement 🌊💞 You guys may have heard me share on this subject before. Its something I am passionate about and apply in my own life. And I want to share with you all why its so meaningful to me. First I want to start with the importance of confidence, the decision to walk through fears, challenges, uncomfortable situations, and to do it with the confidence that allows you to persevere, and the confidence that keeps you going when you cant always see whats waiting in front of you, when you cant foresee if your going to succeed or “fail”. 🧚🏻‍♂️ Too much confidence can hurt you but not enough can kill you. Value yourself authentically and no one will question you, most of all you wont question yourself. Strengthen your weak areas so they cant be used to prevent you from your success. Do this with grace, kindness, patience and an open perspective. Dont have an expectation on what you “deserve”, dont be so fixated on the narrow set of selfish incentives and a self serving me attitude.✨ Comparison is the thief of joy, and I think we should all be careful to trust our purpose, our authentic path’s. In saying that I encourage everyone to take care of themselves, to value their worth, and to create healthy ways of inviting in all the glory of the good stuff and may it be a substainable impact for continued success in your life. 🧚🏻‍♂️🤟🏻 Wishing you all success and happiness.
